				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$99~\%$$\end{document} of the rocks extracted from large-scale and low-grade open-pit operations would be stored either in WRPs or TSFs (Vriens et al. 2020a).Fig. 1
Diagram of an open-pit mine operation and simplified mass balance of wastes and minerals

